--[[Make all guids in this objectTable as non-interactable 
meaning they cannot be manipulated in any way by the players.]]--

--Replace GUIDs with your own!
objectTable = { "9b394b", "6b5d04", "9e9105", "161d4c" }

function onLoad()
    --Loop entries in the object table setting interactable to false
    	for i=1, #objectTable, 1 do	
        		obj = getObjectFromGUID(objectTable[i])
        		if obj ~= nil then
            			obj.interactable = false
        		end
    	end
end

ObjectStates.Name: Custom_Model
ObjectStates.Description:
--------------------

Consult the Selected Scenario for details on creating the mission Disaster and Progression decks from the available Disaster levels.

Cards in a deck should be face-down and cards in discard piles should be face-up. 

Players may examine the cards in a discard pile at any time

If the Location deck is empty and you need to draw from it, shuffle the discard pile to form a new deck.

 If the Disaster deck becomes empty, add 2 cards from the top of the Progression deck to the Disaster deck discard pile and shuffle these cards to form a new Disaster deck.
If the Progression deck is also empty the Academy crumbles and the game is lost.

0.title: Key Points
0.body:
1: PDF of the Core Rulebook: https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B9XeBXHwfx_8MkQtX1FOcGpGZUE/view?usp=sharing

2: PDF of the Grimoire Rulebook: https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B9XeBXHwfx_8OFJjNU5ZWURlNVE/view?usp=sharing 

3. How to play video:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CA3T1aagGJg

4: To Randomise the rooms in the Academy, ensure only room tiles are present on the game board then double tap "F4" and right click on the Randomise zone that appears. 

Tap "F1" to hide the Randomise zone when done.

5: Randomly rotate all the rooms by group selecting the room tiles and tapping "R"

Rooms can be individually rotated at any time by changing their state.

Facing State,  1 = North
                       2 = East
                       3 = South
                       4 = West

6:  Remove excess Mana from the Mana Well to match your Scenario's allocation.

After the rooms have been set, place the Mana Well in the centre of the Mana Crystal room and draw from it as and when Mana is expended.

If the Supply of Mana should ever fall to Zero . . . You have lost the Game.

7: Consult the Selected Scenario for details on creating the mission Disaster and Progression decks from the available Disaster levels.

8: Spell and Disaster cards required in the basic game are marked by an icon in the bottom right corner to make them easy to Identify and can be found at the top of the starting card piles.

9: Cards in a deck should be face-down and cards in discard piles should be face-up. 

10: Players may examine the cards in a discard pile at any time.

11: If the Disaster deck becomes empty, add 2 cards from the top of the Progression deck to the Disaster deck discard pile and shuffle these cards to form a new Disaster deck.

If the Progression deck is also empty, the Academy crumbles and the game is lost.

12: If the Location deck is empty and you need to draw from it, shuffle the discard pile to form a new deck.

13: The corridors are on the board between the rooms.

Corridors start locked and face down. Mouse over them, then Press L to unlock and then F to flip them. 

14: Please consult the Core Rule Book and Grimoire for comprehensive instructions on preparing and playing Wizard's Academy.
